<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>Kick is not a magical attack - Not for Rangers or anybody else</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois.cgi?Shakith">Shakith</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 9:39 a.m. 30/7/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> Kick is not a magical attack - Not for Rangers or anybody else<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/images/datel.gif" width=46 height=22 border=0><img src="http://www.everworld.net/images/dateblnk.gif" width=100 height=22 border=0><img src="http://www.everworld.net/images/dater.gif" width=306 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/forum/common.cgi?read=5780" TARGET=_self>Warriors, rangers, hybrids and a few solutions.</A> (BattleDragon)
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#F4D99F FACE=arial>
<P>Before you flame me I'm not referring to the magical attacks of Monks ... I'm referring to the Kick ability. Even for monks the regular kick they use up to level 5 is not magical.

<P>As for the rest of your post:
<BR>a) I assume you had not seen the latest patch when you made it.
<P>b) Waaaaaaaaa.
<P>'nuff said.
<P>Shak (the man who really hate the "Grass is always greener" class whiners)
<P>&gt; Why is it that other hybrids only get double
<BR>&gt; attack or dual wield, while rangers get
<BR>&gt; double attack & dual wield, they also
<BR>&gt; get kick to attack magical guys, while large
<BR>&gt; warriors can't slam magical guys. Im not
<BR>&gt; suggesting that rangers be weakened, since
<BR>&gt; they don't get plate i consider giving them
<BR>&gt; both of the attacks a good trade-off. but
<BR>&gt; rangers are 3/4 warrior, yet there attacking
<BR>&gt; capabilities are exactly the same, same caps
<BR>&gt; in almost all melee skills + spells. But
<BR>&gt; warriors should be stronger. These are what
<BR>&gt; i suggest
<BR>&gt; 1) Extra attack for every 10 levels starting
<BR>&gt; at 30 with triple hit, and going on with 4
<BR>&gt; hits and 5 hits. Doing this with warriors
<BR>&gt; would make them more formidabble to fight
<BR>&gt; mobs without having 20 of them taking on 1
<BR>&gt; mob.
<BR>&gt; 2) Warriors need 10-20 hp's extra a level,
<BR>&gt; 3-5 hp's a level does not effect us enough
<BR>&gt; to make a difference.
<BR>&gt; 3) Make it possible to use slam/bash &
<BR>&gt; kick at the same time, Yes i know that means
<BR>&gt; monks can use all their special attack, but
<BR>&gt; that would keep them doing more dmg than a
<BR>&gt; warrior with 5attacks, up to 10 with double
<BR>&gt; hit a round.
<BR>&gt; 4) Add another off-hand attack. Like head
<BR>&gt; butt or sucker punch, that can stun and do a
<BR>&gt; nice amount of dmg(10-20).
<BR>&gt; 5) Give more class related armor types at
<BR>&gt; ALL levels, not just high lvl's so that ALL
<BR>&gt; classes can look unique at ALL lvl's.
<BR>&gt; Warriors have the possibiltiy of being the
<BR>&gt; most fun and most played class, which they
<BR>&gt; should be, since they are the core of a
<BR>&gt; group and the core of every other RPG I have
<BR>&gt; played. I'm not suggesting weakening any
<BR>&gt; melee classes to make warriors more
<BR>&gt; powerfull, just make warriors better. If
<BR>&gt; Verant would stop worrying about casters and
<BR>&gt; making everyone like them, then they could
<BR>&gt; start fixing up the base of a group. Right
<BR>&gt; now rangers/paladins/sk's are the prefered
<BR>&gt; tanks for most groups at most lvl's since
<BR>&gt; they can do the same dmg, and heal
<BR>&gt; themselves in 1 fashion or another, but they
<BR>&gt; are 3/4 warrior, so they should be 25%
<BR>&gt; weaker than a warrior, not equal. Exp hits
<BR>&gt; do not make a class weaker, they just make
<BR>&gt; it longer to lvl. Many mid- high lvl
<BR>&gt; warriors are dumping there warrior classes
<BR>&gt; since they have nothing to look forward too
<BR>&gt; after 25-30. Disarm might have been a good
<BR>&gt; skill if it worked on magical weapons, but
<BR>&gt; paying 10$ a month to have the sole purpose
<BR>&gt; of absorbing dmg, is not what verant should
<BR>&gt; be looking for. Warriors should be the class
<BR>&gt; that takes dmg, but they should also be fun
<BR>&gt; to play with multiple attacks and many other
<BR>&gt; skills. Please respond to what I had to say,
<BR>&gt; My ideas have been well thought out and I
<BR>&gt; have chatted with many many warriors/hybrids
<BR>&gt; and casters. I know the arguments why
<BR>&gt; warriors shouldn't be more powerfull, and
<BR>&gt; really i find most of them are weak. Hybrids
<BR>&gt; should be weaker than rogues, in my opinion,
<BR>&gt; since rogues are a pure melee, while hybrids
<BR>&gt; are only part melee, but as it seems hybrids
<BR>&gt; are more than pure melee.
<BR>&gt; BattleDragon
<BR>&gt; Bazil Broketail
<BR>&gt; Barbarian/Dwarf/Human/Dark Elf/Half
<BR>&gt; Elf/Troll/Ogre warrior
<BR>&gt; Test/Cazic Thule/Tallon Zek
<BR>
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
